<item>
            <title>[LU-17338] kernel update [RHEL 8.9 4.18.0-513.9.1.el8_9]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17338</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: bpf: Incorrect verifier pruning leads to unsafe code paths being incorrectly marked as safe (CVE-2023-2163)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: tun: bugs for oversize packet when napi frags enabled in tun_napi_alloc_frags (CVE-2023-3812)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use after free in nvmet_tcp_free_crypto in NVMe (CVE-2023-5178)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use-after-free due to race condition occurring in dvb_register_device() (CVE-2022-45884)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use-after-free due to race condition occurring in dvb_net.c (CVE-2022-45886)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use-after-free due to race condition occurring in dvb_ca_en50221.c (CVE-2022-45919)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: use-after-free in smb2_is_status_io_timeout() (CVE-2023-1192)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bug Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Random delay receiving packets after bringing up VLAN on top of VF with vf-vlan-pruning enabled (BZ#2240750)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bpf_jit_limit hit again (BZ#2243011)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;HPE Edgeline 920t resets during kdump context when ice driver is loaded and when system is booted with intel_iommu=on iommu=pt (BZ#2244625)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2023:7549&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2023:7549&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
